{
  "texts": [
    "There are two types: experiences with 3 Degrees of Freedom (3DoF) and experiences with 6 Degrees of Freedom (6DoF).",
    "These degrees of freedom determine the user's freedom of movement in the VW.• 3DoF: the user can interact with the environment by rotating the view, but the user cannot move around the VW.",
    "The 3 degrees correspond to the rotation of the 3 spatial axes.",
    "• 6DoF: not only can the user rotate the view, but the user can also move around the VW in all directions.",
    "This type of movement usually generates a greater sense of immersion."
  ]
}